cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CE, cs.NE 

This paper deals with the development of an artificial pancreas for Type 1 diabetes mellitus treatment, which involves the use of advanced data-driven non-linear identification techniques to design accurate closed-loop controllers to regulate the glucose level in the blood. This problem is related to the field of control systems (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.LG), as well as artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computational engineering (cs.CE). Additionally, the use of non-linear models to describe the insulin-glucose system is relevant to the field of neural engineering (cs.NE).
